rigins-of-ethernet","line":13,"column":0,"depth":3},"how-should-devices-access-the-network":{"type":"header","text":"How should devices access the network?","value":"how-should-devices-access-the-network","line":19,"column":0,"depth":3},"csmacd":{"type":"header","text":"CSMA/CD","value":"csmacd","line":32,"column":0,"depth":3},"collision-domains":{"type":"header","text":"Collision Domains","value":"collision-domains","line":45,"column":0,"depth":3},"collision-domains-on-devlogswitches":{"type":"header","text":"Collision Domains on devlog.Switches","value":"collision-domains-on-devlogswitches","line":55,"column":0,"depth":3},"collision-domains-on-devloghubs":{"type":"header","text":"Collision Domains on devlog.Hubs","value":"collision-domains-on-devloghubs","line":63,"column":0,"depth":3},"speed-limitations":{"type":"header","text":"Speed Limitations","value":"speed-limitations","line":74,"column":0,"depth":3},"distance-limitations":{"type":"header","text":"Distance Limitations","value":"distance-limitations","line":118,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"9gtn7g40cvqui0sifl1s7t5","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"ethernet\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#ethernet\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Ethernet</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>IEEE 802.3 standard</li>\n<li>In early computer networks, there were many different network technologies competing for a portion of the market share</li>\n<li>Ethernet, Token Ring, FDDI and others fought for dominance</li>\n<li>Currently, Ethernet is dominant for Layer 1</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"origins-of-ethernet\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#origins-of-ethernet\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Origins of Ethernet</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Was first run over <a href=\"/notes/ypv51xf9vfv0r5h66ek30cj\">Coax</a> cables (10Base5, 10Base2), using vampire taps, BNC connectors.</li>\n<li>Ethernet has changed to using <a href=\"/notes/q6rcmbb4k2on7oh9zfm90ba\">Twisted Pair</a> cables using <a href=\"/notes/2xucu5yaqtnegnuf5p40j43\">UTP</a>, <a href=\"/notes/mfu7kh5sjdof5wk03rf0pl0\">STP</a></li>\n<li>10BASE-T is <a href=\"/notes/2xucu5yaqtnegnuf5p40j43\">UTP</a> - max speed 10 Mbps and max distance 100 meters, this is clearly not enough</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"how-should-devices-access-the-network\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#how-should-devices-access-the-network\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>How should devices access the network?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Deterministic\n<ul>\n<li>Very organized and orderly</li>\n<li>Need an electronic token to transmit</li>\n<li>For example: Token Ring</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Contention-based\n<ul>\n<li>Very chaotic</li>\n<li>Transmit (almost) whenever you want</li>\n<li>For example: <a href=\"/notes/co4eno6fzx5ov2408cmwe3w\">Ethernet</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"csmacd\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#csmacd\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>CSMA/CD</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/co4eno6fzx5ov2408cmwe3w\">Ethernet</a> devices transmit based on a principle called Carrier Sense Multiple Access/Collision Detect or CSMA/CD</li>\n<li>Carrier Sense\n<ul>\n<li>Listen to the wire, verify it is not busy</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Multiple Access\n<ul>\n<li>All devices have access at any time</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Collision Detect\n<ul>\n<li>If two deviecs transmit at the same time, a collision occurs</li>\n<li>Back off, wait a random time and try again</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"collision-domains\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#collision-domains\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Collision Domains</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Comprised of all devices on shared <a href=\"/notes/co4eno6fzx5ov2408cmwe3w\">Ethernet</a> segment (everything on same cable or <a href=\"/notes/pkic9qil8dq2q3bqmk01047\">Hub</a>)</li>\n<li>Devices operate at half-duplex when connected to a <a href=\"/notes/pkic9qil8dq2q3bqmk01047\">Hub</a> (Layer 1 Device)</li>\n<li>Devices must listen before they transmit to avoid collisions when operating as <code>CSMA/CD</code></li>\n<li>The larger the Collision Domain, the more chaos in the network.</li>\n<li>Collision Domains need to broken down into smaller chunks for more efficiency</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"collision-domains-on-switches\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#collision-domains-on-switches\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Collision Domains on <a href=\"/notes/arlkpmdlwn4hm2n8iu7gmgs\">Switch</a>es</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/co4eno6fzx5ov2408cmwe3w\">Ethernet</a> <a href=\"/notes/arlkpmdlwn4hm2n8iu7gmgs\">Switch</a>es increase scalability of the network by creating multiple collision domains</li>\n<li>Each port on a switch is a Collision Domain, no chance of collisions and increases speed</li>\n<li>Switches can operate in full-duplex mode</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"collision-domains-on-hubs\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#collision-domains-on-hubs\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Collision Domains on <a href=\"/notes/pkic9qil8dq2q3bqmk01047\">Hub</a>s</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/pkic9qil8dq2q3bqmk01047\">Hub</a>s were used to connect multiple network segments together</li>\n<li>Each <a href=\"/notes/j5t6dogng1gdpuzlgd34t7g\">LAN</a> segment becomes a separate <a href=\"/notes/uirqzeld6hvqmdshssza5we\">Collision Domains</a></li>\n<li>As the network gets larger in which a <a href=\"/notes/pkic9qil8dq2q3bqmk01047\">Hub</a> is being utilized to connect all the machines, the network will get more chaotic as <a href=\"/notes/pkic9qil8dq2q3bqmk01047\">Hub</a> don't break up <a href=\"/notes/uirqzeld6hvqmdshssza5we\">Collision Domains</a>, it'll be treated as one large collision domain.</li>\n<li>To deal with this issue a <a href=\"/notes/irv3o7df3ch6a2lte4twi4t\">Bridge</a> needs to be introduced to the network.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zubayrrr/twiki/main/bin/image.cqfqt7rooe6.png\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"speed-limitations\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#speed-limitations\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Speed Limitations</h3>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"header\">\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">Ethernet Type</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">Bandwidth Capacity</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Ethernet</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">10 Mbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">10 million bits per second</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Fast Ethernet</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100 Mbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100 million bits per second</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Gigabit Ethernet</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1000 Mbps (I Gbps)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1 billion bits per second</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">10-Gigabit Ethernet</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">10 Gbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">10 billion bits per second</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100-Gigabit Ethernet</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100 Gbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100 billion bits per second</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n<li>Bandwidth is the measure of how many bits the network can transmit in 1-second (bps)</li>\n<li>Type of cable determines the bandwidth capacity of the network</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"distance-limitations\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#distance-limitations\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Distance Limitations</h3>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"header\">\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">Ethernet Standard</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: right;\">Media Type</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">Bandwidth Capacity</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">Distance Limitation</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">10BASE-T</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">Cat 3 or Higher</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">10 Mbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100 m</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100BASE-TX</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">Cat 5 or Higher</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100 Mbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100 m</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1000BASE-TX</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">Cat 6 or Higher</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1 Gbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100 m</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1000BASE-SX</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"#MMF\" class=\"tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves\">MMF</a></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1 Gbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">220 m</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1000BASE-LX</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"#MMF\" class=\"tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves\">MMF</a></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1 Gbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">550 m</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"even\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1000BASE-LX</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"#SMF\" class=\"tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves\">SMF</a></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1 Gbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">5 km</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">100BASE-ZX</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"#SMF\" class=\"tc-tiddlylink tc-tiddlylink-resolves\">SMF</a></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">1 Gbps</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">70 km</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n<li>Type of cable determines the distance limitation of the network</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/ypv51xf9vfv0r5h66ek30cj\">Coax</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/uirqzeld6hvqmdshssza5we\">Collision Domains</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/z130icy9h0z0gwz9szs6ngb\">CSMA/CD</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/co4eno6fzx5ov2408cmwe3w\">Ethernet</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/c9g20eqnpm4oaqey6blx497\">GBIC</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/pkic9qil8dq2q3bqmk01047\">Hub</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/4lr9cfvrkbkc8ycvmzpgs8p\">Media Converters</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/xt1xit1xj5isuzst3kxl7o1\">Network Geography</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/h9fwgm5qmlznj6jloqqqlfl\">Network Interface Layer - TCP/IP</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/ck6ds17ovyjf6n0sidmat7v\">Networking in Linux</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/yjeoqhn1zs6blkof49hvacr\">Physical Layer - OSI</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/tac1mkby814gjgwiw72wyzp\">Transceivers</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/q6rcmbb4k2on7oh9zfm90ba\">Twisted Pair</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"3nfl4nvv516muyzozhcwrw8","title":"/root","desc":"","updated":1655559901157,"created":1637610830605,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"Dendron"},"contentHash":"581715455a6f0f7a699209e8521b4acf","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"3nfl4nvv516muyzozhcwrw8","vaultName":"Dendron"},"value":"archive.about","alias":"my","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":